Often an exclamatory Japanese phrase with the english equivalent of a "Bulls-Eye",or a perfectly precise target acquisition. Zuboshi is often used as Japanese slang in daily conversation to indicate whether or not  a discussion point has been fully understood by another. Zuboshi is used widely in the U.S. by Japanese-Americans and is often expressed in its Romaji form. See "Hepburn romanization" for more information on written Japanese. 

